### Getting started with this project

This project will be a next.js application, built on React.

To create a react app, you need to create the following folders and files in your repository:

- 📁 app
    - layout.jsx
    - page.jsx
    - 📁 components
        - Footer.jsx
        - Header.jsx
    - 📁 Data
        - Data1.jsx
        - Data1.json
        - Data2.jsx
        - Data2.jsx
- 🔧 .env.development
- 🔧 .env.production
- 🔧 .gitignore
- 🔧 package.json

This structure is not in full alphabetical order, as I have tried to make it readable.

Additionally, the data folder is not mandatory for Node.JS, but it is a very helpful tool to implement, as it allows for centralised data management.